  <h1 id="Microsoft_Xna_Framework_GraphicsDeviceManager_IsFullScreen_" data-uid="Microsoft.Xna.Framework.GraphicsDeviceManager.IsFullScreen*" class="text-break">GraphicsDeviceManager.IsFullScreen Property</h1>

  <div class="api">
    <div class="markdown level0 summary"></div>
<div class="markdown level0 conceptual"></div>

  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  




    <div class="markdown level0 summary"><p>Indicates the desire to switch into fullscreen mode.</p>
</div>
    <div class="markdown level0 conceptual"></div>
    
      
        <div class="codewrapper">
          <pre><code class="lang-csharp hljs">public bool IsFullScreen { get; set; }</code></pre>
        </div>
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
    
    <h id="Microsoft_Xna_Framework_GraphicsDeviceManager_IsFullScreen_remarks">Remarks</h>
    <div class="markdown level0 remarks"><p>When called at startup this will automatically set fullscreen mode during initialization.  If
set after startup you must call ApplyChanges() for the fullscreen mode to be changed.
Note that for some platforms that do not support windowed modes this property has no affect.</p>
</div>
    
    
    
    

